## Reference: Gemini CLI pattern

Follow `geminicli/transcript.go` + `geminicli/gemini.go:201-277` + `geminicli/lifecycle.go:16` as the reference implementation. Kiro's format is similar (single JSON blob) but uses paired history entries instead of a flat messages array.

## Kiro Transcript Format (from real SQLite cache)

```json
{
  "conversation_id": "uuid",
  "history": [
    {
      "user": { "content": { "Prompt": { "prompt": "text" } }, "timestamp": "..." },
      "assistant": { "Response": { "message_id": "uuid", "content": "text" } }
    },
    {
      "user": { "content": { "Prompt": { "prompt": "text" } } },
      "assistant": { "ToolUse": { "message_id": "uuid", "tool_uses": [
        { "id": "tu-1", "name": "fs_write", "args": { "path": "/abs/path/file.go", ... } }
      ]}}
    },
    {
      "user": { "content": { "ToolUseResults": { "tool_use_results": [...] } } },
      "assistant": { "Response": { "message_id": "uuid", "content": "Done." } }
    }
  ]
}
```

